    <article id="section-usage">
      <h1 class="app-article-headline hca-typography--headline">Usage</h1>

      <section class="app-section">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="hca-layout__container--body-content">
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">Expansion panels are best suited for mobile devices with small screens to organize content in a way that saves space and enhances the reader's ability to quickly locate key pieces of information.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">The expanded panel itself should only contain secondary information.  Primary information should never be hidden - in expansion panels or otherwise. Do not use expansion panels to clean up large amounts of information or save page space.  Instead, use them to organize information and provide small areas for editable content.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">An expansion panel may use a focus or hover state (by highlighting the chevron) to provide focus to individual list items.</p>
              <p class="hca-typography--body-1">On a keyboard, users may traverse through list items by using the Tab key.  They may expand and collapse the list items using the Enter (or Return) key.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
